<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1049,1629]" pageId="9" pageNumber="560">
<keyLead pageId="9" pageNumber="560">
1 Vestiture dense (
<figureCitation box="[383,455,1049,1071]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1970,1993]" captionTargetBox="[175,1404,195,1944]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[170,1417,183,1964]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Neapion (N.) marquesae sp. nov.: paratype female, dorSal (1) and lateral vieW (2), holotype male, lateral vieW (3); head, paratype female (4) and holotype male, dorSal vieW (5); female, lateral vieW (6)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1209788/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="560">Fig 1-3</figureCitation>
); elytral intervals convex, with raised areas in intervals 2, 4, 5, 6 (
<figureCitation box="[1089,1148,1049,1071]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1970,1993]" captionTargetBox="[175,1404,195,1944]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[170,1417,183,1964]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Neapion (N.) marquesae sp. nov.: paratype female, dorSal (1) and lateral vieW (2), holotype male, lateral vieW (3); head, paratype female (4) and holotype male, dorSal vieW (5); female, lateral vieW (6)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1209788/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="560">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
)................................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName authority="Sousa &amp; Ribeiro-Costa, 2018" authorityName="Sousa &amp; Ribeiro-Costa" authorityYear="2018" box="[1113,1375,1079,1101]" class="Insecta" family="Brentidae" genus="Neapion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="560" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marquesae" status="sp. n." subGenus="Neotropion">
<emphasis box="[1113,1129,1079,1100]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="560">N</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis box="[1149,1257,1079,1100]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="560">Neotropion</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1271,1375,1079,1100]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="560">marquesae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1382,1436,1079,1101]" pageId="9" pageNumber="560" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1382,1436,1079,1101]" pageId="9" pageNumber="560">sp. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1049,1629]" box="[151,1435,1108,1130]" pageId="9" pageNumber="560">
<keyLead box="[151,1435,1108,1130]" pageId="9" pageNumber="560">
- Vestiture sparse; elytral intervals flat, without raised areas (
<figureCitation box="[792,893,1108,1130]" captionStart="FIGURES 15–19" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1970,1993]" captionTargetBox="[198,1393,204,1944]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[178,1413,193,1954]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 15–19. Neapion (N.) diringsi sp. nov.: paratype female, dorSal (15) and lateral vieW (16); Spiculum gaStrale (17); peniS, dorSal vieW (18); tegmen, dorSal vieW (19)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1209794/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="560">Fig 15, 16</figureCitation>
)........................................... 2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="9" pageNumber="560">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1049,1629]" box="[151,1436,1137,1159]" pageId="9" pageNumber="560">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,1137,1159]" pageId="9" pageNumber="560">
2 Rostrum in side view flat ventrally at mesorostral level (
<figureCitation box="[765,837,1137,1159]" captionStart="FIGURES 15–19" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1970,1993]" captionTargetBox="[198,1393,204,1944]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[178,1413,193,1954]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 15–19. Neapion (N.) diringsi sp. nov.: paratype female, dorSal (15) and lateral vieW (16); Spiculum gaStrale (17); peniS, dorSal vieW (18); tegmen, dorSal vieW (19)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1209794/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="560">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
); elytral vestiture with light scales (
<figureCitation box="[1179,1252,1137,1159]" captionStart="FIGURES 15–19" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1970,1993]" captionTargetBox="[198,1393,204,1944]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[178,1413,193,1954]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 15–19. Neapion (N.) diringsi sp. nov.: paratype female, dorSal (15) and lateral vieW (16); Spiculum gaStrale (17); peniS, dorSal vieW (18); tegmen, dorSal vieW (19)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1209794/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="560">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
).............. 3
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1049,1629]" box="[151,1436,1167,1189]" pageId="9" pageNumber="560">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,1167,1189]" pageId="9" pageNumber="560">- Rostrum in side view convex ventrally at mesorostral level; elytral vestiture with light and dark scales.................. 4</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="9" pageNumber="560">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1049,1629]" pageId="9" pageNumber="560">
<keyLead pageId="9" pageNumber="560">
3 Integument dark reddish brown; mesorostrum subequal to width of prorostrum; elytral intervals with scales uniformly arranged; length less than 
<quantity box="[475,533,1225,1247]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="560" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
; pedon in profile with ventral margin at apex produced slightly; internal sac with ‘tuning-fork’ shaped sclerite 515µm long; tegmen with fenestrae narrowly separated, about 0.16 times fenestrae width, prostegium not bifid.................................................................. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Wagner, 1908)" authorityName="Wagner" authorityYear="1908" baseAuthorityName="Wagner" baseAuthorityYear="1908" box="[1003,1435,1284,1306]" class="Insecta" family="Brentidae" genus="Neotropion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="560" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="americanum" subGenus="Neotropion">
<emphasis box="[1003,1019,1285,1306]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="560">N</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis box="[1039,1147,1285,1306]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="560">Neotropion</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1161,1281,1285,1306]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="560">americanum</emphasis>
(Wagner, 1908)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1049,1629]" pageId="9" pageNumber="560">
<keyLead pageId="9" pageNumber="560">
- Integument dark brown; mesorostrum larger than prorostrum; elytral intervals with some dense area of scales, forming one spot on each of intervals 1–4 at posterior median region of elytra (
<figureCitation box="[866,938,1343,1365]" captionStart="FIGURES 15–19" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1970,1993]" captionTargetBox="[198,1393,204,1944]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[178,1413,193,1954]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 15–19. Neapion (N.) diringsi sp. nov.: paratype female, dorSal (15) and lateral vieW (16); Spiculum gaStrale (17); peniS, dorSal vieW (18); tegmen, dorSal vieW (19)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1209794/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="560">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
); length greater than 
<quantity box="[1145,1221,1343,1365]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="9" pageNumber="560" unit="mm" value="2.5">2.5 mm</quantity>
; pedon in profile with ventral margin not produced; internal sac with ‘tuning-fork’ shaped sclerite 680 µm long; tegmen with fenestrae widely separated, about 0.7 times fenestrae width, prostegium medially bifid (
<figureCitation box="[859,928,1401,1423]" captionStart="FIGURES 15–19" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1970,1993]" captionTargetBox="[198,1393,204,1944]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[178,1413,193,1954]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 15–19. Neapion (N.) diringsi sp. nov.: paratype female, dorSal (15) and lateral vieW (16); Spiculum gaStrale (17); peniS, dorSal vieW (18); tegmen, dorSal vieW (19)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1209794/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="560">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
)................ 
<taxonomicName authority="Sousa &amp; Ribeiro-Costa, 2018" authorityName="Sousa &amp; Ribeiro-Costa" authorityYear="2018" box="[1142,1376,1401,1423]" class="Insecta" family="Brentidae" genus="Neapion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="560" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diringsi" status="sp. n." subGenus="Neotropion">
<emphasis box="[1142,1158,1402,1423]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="560">N</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis box="[1179,1287,1402,1423]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="560">Neotropion</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1301,1376,1402,1423]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="560">diringsi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1382,1436,1402,1424]" pageId="9" pageNumber="560" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1382,1436,1402,1424]" pageId="9" pageNumber="560">sp. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="9" pageNumber="560">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1049,1629]" pageId="9" pageNumber="560">
<keyLead pageId="9" pageNumber="560">
4 Scutellum ovate, slightly longer than wide; elytra in profile convex; pedon in profile with dorsal margin at apex produced slightly; internal sac with ‘tuning-fork’ shaped sclerite 455 µm long; tegmen with fenestrae widely separated, about 0.7 times fenestrae width, prostegium not bifid...................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="(Gyllenhal, 1839)" authorityName="Gyllenhal" authorityYear="1839" baseAuthorityName="Gyllenhal" baseAuthorityYear="1839" box="[1032,1436,1489,1511]" class="Insecta" family="Brentidae" genus="Neotropion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="560" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lebasii" subGenus="Neotropion">
<emphasis box="[1032,1052,1490,1511]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="560">N</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis box="[1073,1181,1490,1511]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="560">Neotropion</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1195,1259,1490,1511]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="560">lebasii</emphasis>
(Gyllenhal, 1839)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1049,1629]" pageId="9" pageNumber="560">
<keyLead pageId="9" pageNumber="560">
- Scutellum rectangular, more than twice as long as wide, posteriorly forming slender, awl-shaped projection; elytra in profile acutely gibbose; pedon in profile with dorsal margin not produced; internal sac with ‘tuning-fork’ shaped sclerite 550 µm long; tegmen with fenestrae narrowly separated, about 0.13 times fenestrae width, prostegium medially bifid..................................................................................... 
